  "prompt": "Why did Quora remove the 'needs improvement' tags?",
  "response": "Quora removed the \"needs improvement\" tags in response to user feedback and to create a more constructive environment for content creation. The tags were often seen as discouraging and led to negative experiences for some users, as they could affect users\u2019 contributions and engagement. By removing these tags, Quora aimed to foster a more positive atmosphere, encouraging users to focus on improving their content without the stigma associated with being labeled as needing improvement. This change is part of ongoing efforts to enhance user experience and promote healthy community interactions on the platform.",
